== Meaning ==
[[Image:Göttingen-Beschneidungswerkzeuge.02.JPG|right|thumb|A box of ritual objects a [[Mohel]] would use.  A very old example of an ''Izmel'' appears on the lower-left.  Today's implements are much more precision.  This is from a Göttingen Museum.]]
'''Izmel''' (''[[Hebrew]]:''&nbsp;'', noun'') is a specialized surgical knife used by the ''[[Mohel]]'' in the [[Jewish]] [[circumcision]] ritual of ''[[W:Brit milah|Brit Milah]]'' for infant males.  It must have certain characteristics, per [[W:Jewish law|Jewish Law]], including that it may not stop the flow of blood (unlike the [[constrain|constricting]] devices commonly used by a surgeon or [[urology|Urologist]]).

